## Practical Guidance

**Scenario Design:**
Each scenario should require 2-7 tasks, span 50k-150k tokens, involve 10+ tool calls, and require 1-4 hours execution time. Mix domains (software, research, business, creative) to test generalization. Include ambiguous specifications requiring clarification.

**User Simulation Tuning:**
Feedback should be progressively more detailed; early iterations accept partial work, later iterations demand refinement. Vary feedback style (requests vs. suggestions) to test agent adaptability. Calibrate approval threshold to match real user standards per domain.

**Rubric Calibration:**
Weights differ per deliverable type: code emphasizes functionality, documents emphasize clarity, analysis emphasizes insight. Validate rubrics against human evaluator agreement (aim for >0.8 Spearman correlation). Domain-specific rubrics improve discrimination.

**Capability Mapping:**
Task understanding shows in output quality relative to specification. Planning surfaces in solution structure and dependencies. Tool selection appears in diversity and appropriateness. Feedback integration in responsiveness to corrections. Multi-step reasoning in task chaining. Self-correction in error handling and validation.

**Evaluation Automation:**
Docker sandbox enables deterministic validation (unit tests for code, schema validation for configs). Use checksums for document format consistency. Automated visual comparison for screenshot-based deliverables. Reduces human annotation bottleneck while maintaining rigor.

## Reference

- **Paper:** AgencyBench: Benchmarking the Frontiers of Autonomous Agents in 1M-Token Real-World Contexts (arXiv:2601.11044, January 2026)
- **Scale:** 32 scenarios, 138 tasks, 90 tool calls/task, 1M tokens, multi-hour execution
- **Benchmark:** https://github.com/GAIR-NLP/AgencyBench
- **Key Finding:** Closed-source models (48.4%) significantly outperform open-source (32.1%); stark disparities in feedback-driven self-correction
- **Evaluation:** User simulation + Docker rubrics enable scalable automated assessment without human-in-the-loop bottleneck
